The paper focuses on using machine learning methods for geographical knowledge discovery, specifically using unsupervised learning methods on street level and street network images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also deals with geographical processes and information, indicating that it could also belong to the geographic information systems (cs.GR) sub-category. The use of generative visualizations and embeddings for prediction also suggests that the paper could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistical learning (cs.SI) sub-categories.
